import seaborn as sns
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='miles', y='gas', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the correlation between miles driven and gas used?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data_grouped = data.groupby(data['year'].dt.year)['miles'].mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='year', y='miles', data=data_grouped)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average miles driven per year?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    data['gas_per_mile'] = data['gas'] / data['miles']
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='year', y='gas_per_mile', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the average gas used per mile?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    avg_gas_per_mile = np.mean(data['gas_per_mile'])
    plt.axhline(avg_gas_per_mile, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_gas_per_mile:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```
